NAME
    gcloud alpha storage buckets create - create a new Cloud Storage bucket

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha storage buckets create BUCKET [--location=LOCATION]
        [--requester-pays] [--storage-class=STORAGE_CLASS] [--versioning]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Create a new Cloud Storage bucket.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Bucket resource - The bucket to create. This represents a Cloud resource.
     This must be specified.

       BUCKET
          ID of the bucket or fully qualified identifier for the bucket.

FLAGS
     --location=LOCATION
        The location where object data will reside.

     --requester-pays
        True to make requests for objects in this bucket pay the egress costs.

     --storage-class=STORAGE_CLASS
        This defines how objects in the bucket are stored and determines the
        SLA and the cost of storage. For more information see:
        https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/storage-classes

     --versioning
        Enable object versioning in this bucket.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the storage/v1 API. The full documentation for this API
    can be found at: https://developers.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. If this command fails with API permission errors despite
    specifying the right project, you may be trying to access an API with an
    invitation-only early access allowlist.

